parameters: \N<Seno>Huh!?
\N<Princess Consort Suia>This... What are you...!? Take it off...!

\N<Zuuteruka>Just keep it on for now. You two are about to undertake a
very important role, literally one that could sway the fate
of others, you know?
\N<Seno>Hmph... What an exaggeration...!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, is that so? If you think that, you're free to go
back and rest. But if you really must, I won't stop you?
Hehehe...
\N<Seno>Tch...!
op_スーイアセノ01u

\N<Zuuteruka>There, there, both of you line up and spread your legs
nicely.
\N<Seno>Out of the blue... Don't mess around!

\N<Zuuteruka>Just be good and listen. Acting tough will only lead to
losses, you know?
\N<Seno>Grr...!
op_スーイアセノ01a
\N<Princess Consort Suia>...!?
\N<Zuuteruka>That's right, just like that. Isn't it a nice view?
\N<Seno>Wha... What the! What's going on...!?

Voices of many people can be heard around them. However,
with the strange masks made by Luda on their faces, they
can neither hear clearly nor look around.

Several men stand before the two of them. Eventually, one of
them raises his voice loudly.

\N<The Man Before Me>Zuuteruka! What are you planning...!? Are you trying to
appease us by providing women!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Well now, that's a good question. But I think even stiff-
headed guys like you would benefit from sticking around
until the end today, as fellow men?
\N<The Man Before Me>What did you say...!?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Gah...! Zuuteruka! What's happening! What do you intend to
do...!?
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, you can take it off soon. Don't be shocked, okay?
op_スーイアセノ01b
\N<Seno>Wha...!!??
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Th-This is...!!??
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>Pr-Princess Consort... and Lady Seno too...

Princess Consort Suia and Seno. In front of them, dressed in
lewd and provocative outfits, stood a crowd of men.

They were the remnants of the defeated nation, once known as
"Dawn's Ear", now overrun by Luda.
\N<Princess Consort Suia>No... Ahh!!??

The remnants were once subjects or subordinates to the two
of them. Now, in front of these subordinates, they felt the
misery of exposing themselves in such a lewd manner and
reached the peak of their shame.
セノ3_2
\N<Seno>Gah...!!?? What in the world is this...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hey hey, don't hide it. Show it off properly? Give something
back to the guys who gathered here especially for this.
公妃3_3
\N<Princess Consort Suia>A return favor...!? What on earth for...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... You both know, right? The people here are soldiers
who were driven out of their country by Luda.

\N<Zuuteruka>They're all brave warriors who fought desperately against
Luda and got injured. In other words, loyal and brave men.
セノ3_2

\N<Seno>Why bring that up now...! I know that without you telling
me! What exactly is this all about...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>These are the soldiers who once dedicated their lives to you
two. And they're the ones who haven't sworn allegiance to
Luda.
公妃3_3
\N<Princess Consort Suia>Eh...?
セノ3_2
\N<Seno>Zuuteruka, you... don't tell me...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, exactly. From now on, use yourselves to persuade
them to surrender to Luda. Otherwise, they'll all be
hanged.
公妃3_3

\N<Princess Consort Suia>That's absurd... Stop it! The war is over! There's no point
in exchanging lives anymore, right!?

\N<Zuuteruka>That's a discussion I can't have. But I'm not a demon, you
know. That's why I called you two here. Do you understand?
公妃3_3

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Our persuasion is the last chance to save their lives... Is
that what you mean!? How far will you go...!

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>The war is over...! What do you mean, Princess Consort?
We... we haven't lost yet! We can still fight!
op_スーイアセノ01b

Watching the exchange from below the stage, a former duchy
soldier raises his voice louder than the rest. His call is
followed by many voices of agreement.

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>That's right! Let's fight! It's better to die fighting than
to surrender to Luda!
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... well said. Shall I grant your wish then?
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>Zuuteruka...! You traitor! Have you no shame!!
\N<Seno>You guys...

\N<Zuuteruka>What will you do? I think it's foolish, but their spirit and
loyalty are admirable. They'd rather die than surrender.
\N<Seno>Gah...!
\N<Princess Consort Suia>...
op_スーイアセノ16a

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Please listen. Right now, there is only one command I can
give you as the Princess Consort.

Princess Consort Suia, who had been silently observing the
exchange, finally speaks up. The defeated soldiers, once her
subjects, reflexively close their mouths and wait for her
next words.
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>Princess Consort...?

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Everyone... as Zuuteruka said, I want you to surrender to
Luda's forces. Please... value your lives.

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>Princess Consort... we can still fight! We prefer the call
to battle over an order to surrender!!
\N<Princess Consort Suia>...
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>Princess Consort!!

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>That's right... what about Lord Orugi!? If Lord Orugi is
still alive, we can turn the situation around...!

The name of Orugi, Seno's husband and former leader of the
self-defense force, is raised among the defeated soldiers. A
faint hope swells in their hearts that if he is alive, they
might still be able to rebuild their army.
op_スーイアセノ01b
\N<Seno>My husband... he's dead. He's no longer in this world.
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>Eh...!!??

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>No, that's a lie... then, Lady Seno, you take his place...!
Take revenge...!
\N<Seno>...

The voices yearning for Seno, Orugi's wife and former deputy
leader, to rise up. At the same time, a white cloudy liquid
drips from her vagina, seemingly a testament to her status
as Luda's mistress.
\N<Seno>...I'm sorry. I'm so sorry... everyone.
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>No way... that means... both of you have already...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, what are you so surprised about? It's only natural
for women who sided with a defeated army to end up like
this.

\N<Zuuteruka>Surely you didn't think that these two remained pure since
the day the castle fell?
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>Gah...! You bastard...!!

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>That's right! Lord Yuia...! Lord Yuia is still here! I heard
that the Grand Duke has passed away, but his son, Lord Yuia,
is still alive...!
op_スーイアセノ16a

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Of course Yuia is... I also believe that my son is alive.
No, he must be alive.

\N<Princess Consort Suia>And he must be concerned about us. Knowing how clever he is,
he might soon be preparing his army to come here...
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>If that's the case... until that day we will...!

\N<Princess Consort Suia>Continue fighting? That cannot be... Until that day comes,
more lives will be lost. Please don't make me choose any
more sorrowful options...
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>Princess Consort...
\N<Princess Consort Suia>...
\N<Seno>...

The room falls silent at Suia's words. The presence or
absence of a will to fight, the possibility of defeating
Luda - such discussions are moot when the provocative
appearance of the two women speaks volumes about the current
situation.
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>...
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>I will surrender to Luda's forces.

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>What did you say!? You traitor!! Are you in league with that
Zuuteruka!?

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>No! It's meaningless to pledge loyalty to a fallen nation!
Wouldn't it be true loyalty to wait for an opportunity to
live on!?

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>You won't listen! That's nothing but the sophistry of
cowards!

\N<Former Duchy Soldier>That's not true! Think about it, everyone! Can anyone here
confidently say that dying here wouldn't be a dog's death!?
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>Grr...!!

\N<Seno>Everyone... I want you to listen. This is the last request
from me and Princess Consort Suia.

\N<Seno>No one's choice here is wrong. But... surrendering to the
enemy requires even more courage than fighting.

\N<Seno>It might sound convenient, but... I want everyone to
understand...
\N<Former Duchy Soldier>...
